# =============================================================================
# Taktology — a minimal, research-grounded vocabulary for takt production planning
# =============================================================================
#
# v0.5.0 — MINIMAL CORE, aligned to the Digital Twin Construction (DTC) ontology v2
#          and to the TopologicPy ontology (top:) v0.2.0 — including its new graph
#          layer (top:Graph / top:KnowledgeGraph), which is what a TGraph-built takt
#          plan projects into.
#
# What this is
#   The canonical takt skeleton: 5 classes, 8 object properties, 6 datatype
#   properties (19 terms). It adds ONLY what existing ontologies lack — the takt
#   type-layer (wagon), the takt rhythm, the takt-plan graph — and reuses the DTC
#   ontology for the process / zone / resource backbone and BOT for topology.
#
# How it composes (alignment by REFERENCE, not owl:imports — keeps it lightweight)
#   dtc:  DTC ontology v2 (namespace .../ontology/v2#)  -> rdfs:subClassOf / subPropertyOf
#         (process, working-zone, resource and schedule backbone; imports BOT 0.3.2)
#   bot:  Building Topology Ontology                    -> rdfs:subClassOf for TaktZone
#         (adjacency via bot:adjacentZone, containment via bot:containsElement/containsZone)
#   top:  TopologicPy ontology v0.2.0 (w3id.org/topologicpy#)
#         -> rdfs:subClassOf for TaktGraph (top:KnowledgeGraph); skos:relatedMatch for
#         TaktZone (top:Zone). TopologicPy's TGraph computes the geometry and emits the graph.
#   ifc:  IFC4 ifcOWL (ADD2_TC1 — the published ifcOWL) -> skos:closeMatch on classes;
#         objectified IfcRel* relationships are referenced by rdfs:seeAlso (a property
#         and a relationship-entity live at different metamodel levels).
#   Every term carries dcterms:source -> the research corpus that grounds it, and
#   rdfs:isDefinedBy -> this ontology.
#
# Why DTC v2 (supersedes the v0.4.x alignment to DTC v1; see docs ADR-12)
#   v2 restructures the process backbone: Process > AsPlannedProcess/AsPerformedProcess
#   (WorkPackage/Activity/Task are gone), hasTarget and isPerformedIn take domain
#   Process (level-correct for a takt task), ConstructionSchedule models the plan,
#   and the as-planned/as-performed split is the natural seam for takt CONTROL later.
#   v2 imports BOT, so dtc: and bot: compose by design.
#
# Honest scope notes
#   - DTC reifies sequencing (hasPrecondition -> ProcessPrecondition + requiresProcess
#     + hasSequenceType) and resource assignment (hasResourceAssignment -> ResourceAssignment
#     -> requiresResource). Takt uses simpler DIRECT edges (hasSuccessor, performedBy);
#     these are rdfs:seeAlso-related to DTC, not subproperties, because the shapes differ.
#   - DTC has no occurrence-type layer (its Type class is an enumeration base for
#     status/sequence types); takt:WagonType fills that gap (closeMatch ifc:IfcTaskType).
#   - dtc:startTime / dtc:endTime are AS-PERFORMED observations in DTC (both versions).
#     Do NOT use them for planned dates. Planned task dates DERIVE from the plan:
#     takt:planStart + (takt:slot - 1) x takt:taktDuration. As-performed control data
#     belongs on the DTC as-performed side, outside this core (see docs ADR-14/ADR-16).
#   - Upstream ontology versions this file was verified against are pinned in
#     ontology/alignments.lock.json and checked by scripts/validate.py.
#
# License: CC BY 4.0 (see LICENSE).
# =============================================================================

@prefix takt:    <https://w3id.org/taktology#> .
@prefix dtc:     <https://dtc-ontology.cms.ed.tum.de/ontology/v2#> .
@prefix top:     <http://w3id.org/topologicpy#> .
@prefix bot:     <https://w3id.org/bot#> .
@prefix ifc:     <https://standards.buildingsmart.org/IFC/DEV/IFC4/ADD2_TC1/OWL#> .
@prefix owl:     <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf:     <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:    <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos:    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix xsd:     <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix vann:    <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/> .

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
<https://w3id.org/taktology> a owl:Ontology ;
    dcterms:title "Taktology — takt production planning vocabulary (minimal core)"@en ;
    dcterms:license <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> ;
    dcterms:created "2026-06-23"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:modified "2026-07-01"^^xsd:date ;
    dcterms:creator "Byggstyrning AB"@en ;
    owl:versionInfo "0.5.0" ;
    owl:versionIRI <https://w3id.org/taktology/0.5.0> ;
    owl:priorVersion <https://w3id.org/taktology/0.4.1> ;
    vann:preferredNamespacePrefix "takt" ;
    vann:preferredNamespaceUri "https://w3id.org/taktology#" ;
    rdfs:comment """Minimal core takt-planning vocabulary. Specializes the Digital
        Twin Construction (DTC) ontology v2 for takt, places takt zones in the BOT
        topology graph, types the takt plan as a TopologicPy knowledge graph, and
        adds the takt-specific type-layer and rhythm. Aligned to IFC4 ifcOWL by
        skos:closeMatch (classes) and rdfs:seeAlso (objectified IfcRel* relations).
        Alignment is by reference (no owl:imports) to stay lightweight."""@en ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://dtc-ontology.cms.ed.tum.de/ontology/v2/> ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <http://w3id.org/topologicpy> ;
    rdfs:seeAlso <https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-3824/paper3.pdf> .

# =============================================================================
# CLASSES (5)
# =============================================================================

takt:TaktZone a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf bot:Zone ,                    # SPATIAL: lives in the BOT topology graph — adjacency (bot:adjacentZone), containment (bot:containsElement), nesting (bot:containsZone)
                    dtc:AsPlannedWorkingZone ;    # PROCESS: a planned LBS working zone (DTC v2)
    rdfs:label "Takt zone"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A spatial work area through which takt wagons flow at a fixed
        rhythm — often a half-floor, fire compartment or room cluster. Deliberately
        BOTH a bot:Zone (3D extent, adjacency via bot:adjacentZone, element containment
        via bot:containsElement, zone nesting via bot:containsZone for the macro/norm/
        micro levels of the three-level method) AND a DTC planned working zone (the
        LBS / process semantics). DTC itself keeps the two apart — its WorkingZone is
        NOT a bot:Zone; it only dtc:alignsWithZone one. Takt collapses that separation
        on purpose: in takt planning, space IS the resource, so the planned work area
        is delineated as a spatial zone (documented divergence; consumers who need
        DTC's separation can mirror it with dtc:alignsWithZone — see docs ADR-13).
        When the zone is computed by TopologicPy, instances may additionally be typed
        top:Zone; the class itself only relatedMatches it (a takt zone need not be a
        TopologicPy topology)."""@en ;
    skos:closeMatch ifc:IfcSpatialZone ;
    skos:relatedMatch top:Zone ;
    rdfs:seeAlso dtc:alignsWithZone ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1350> ,        # dlouhy-2016-three-level (zone hierarchy)
                   <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/902> ,         # frandson-2013-cladding
                   <https://doi.org/10.3233/SW-200385> .           # rasmussen-2020-bot (extend bot:Zone)

takt:WagonType a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Wagon type"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The reusable definition of one trade's work package — e.g.
        'Enkling gipsväggar' (single-side drywall). The TYPE level; its per-zone
        occurrences are takt:TaktTask, linked by takt:instantiates. DTC has no
        occurrence-type layer (dtc:Type is an enumeration base for status/sequence
        types, not task types), so this term has no DTC parent and aligns only to
        IFC's type mechanism."""@en ;
    skos:closeMatch ifc:IfcTaskType ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> ,      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (activity structure)
                   <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1482> .        # tommelein-2017 (work packaging, non-repetitive takt)

takt:TaktTask a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf dtc:AsPlannedProcess ;
    rdfs:label "Takt task"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """One occurrence: one wagon performed in one takt zone for one takt
        (one coloured cell of the plan grid). A DTC v2 AsPlannedProcess is 'an
        as-planned process that is part of a construction schedule' — exactly what a
        takt task is. Carries its slot in the rhythm and acts on a trade-specific
        subset of the zone's elements. Degenerate cells are flagged, not subclassed:
        takt:isMilestone for milestone cells, takt:isBuffer for capacity-buffer cells
        (empty wagons) — a documented pragmatism mirroring IfcTask.IsMilestone."""@en ;
    skos:closeMatch ifc:IfcTask ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt

takt:Crew a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf dtc:AsPlannedWorkerCrew ;
    rdfs:label "Crew"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """A planned worker crew (gang) that performs takt tasks; the crew
        codes in a takt plan. DTC v2 keeps as-planned and as-performed crews disjoint;
        this is the PLANNED crew — observed crews belong on the as-performed side."""@en ;
    skos:closeMatch ifc:IfcCrewResource ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (MA/Kol)

takt:TaktGraph a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf top:KnowledgeGraph ,          # a semantic graph a TopologicPy TGraph emits/consumes
                    dtc:ConstructionSchedule ;    # the schedule aggregating the plan's processes
    rdfs:label "Takt graph"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The takt plan itself, as a graph: the coloured wagon-x-zone grid
        plus its rhythm. Doubles as (a) a top:KnowledgeGraph — the thing a TopologicPy
        TGraph-built takt plan projects into (nodes/relationships via top:hasNode /
        top:hasRelationship), and (b) a dtc:ConstructionSchedule — so plan membership
        is dtc:hasProcess (TaktGraph -> TaktTask), reused rather than minted. Carries
        the plan-wide beat (takt:taktDuration) and the calendar anchor
        (takt:planStart). Supersedes ADR-7's 'plan container stays out of the core':
        the TGraph pairing gave the container a concrete job."""@en ;
    skos:closeMatch ifc:IfcWorkSchedule ;
    rdfs:seeAlso dtc:hasProcess ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <http://w3id.org/topologicpy> ,                 # topologicpy-ontology v0.2.0 (Graph/KnowledgeGraph layer)
                   <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (the plan grid)

# =============================================================================
# OBJECT PROPERTIES (8)
# =============================================================================

takt:instantiates a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "instantiates"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Links a takt task occurrence to the wagon type it realises. No
        DTC equivalent (DTC has no occurrence-type layer). Buffer cells
        (takt:isBuffer true) typically instantiate nothing."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:WagonType ;
    rdfs:seeAlso ifc:IfcRelDefinesByType ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> ,      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (template -> occurrence)
                   <https://technical.buildingsmart.org/standards/ifc/ifc-formats/ifcowl/> .

takt:performedIn a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf dtc:isPerformedIn ;
    rdfs:label "performed in"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The takt zone a task is located in — the work AREA, which generally
        contains elements for several trades, not only this task's. For the operand,
        use takt:actsOn. Specializes dtc:isPerformedIn (v2: Process -> WorkingZone;
        level-correct since TaktTask is an AsPlannedProcess and TaktZone an
        AsPlannedWorkingZone)."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:TaktZone ;
    rdfs:seeAlso ifc:IfcRelAssignsToProduct ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1181> .        # frandson-2015-lbms-vs-takt (space as resource)

takt:actsOn a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf dtc:hasTarget ;
    rdfs:label "acts on"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The building element(s) this task constructs, installs or operates
        on — the OPERAND, distinct from the zone it sits in (takt:performedIn). A
        trade-specific SUBSET of the zone's contents: anything computed per trade
        (work density, duration checks) reads this operand, not the zone total.
        Specializes dtc:hasTarget (v2: Process -> bot:Element). Deliberately broader
        than DTC's/IFC's 'resulting product' phrasing: covers produced AND
        operated-on elements (documented divergence, see docs ADR-4)."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  bot:Element ;
    rdfs:seeAlso ifc:IfcRelAssignsToProduct ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1061/(ASCE)CO.1943-7862.0002398> .   # tommelein-2022-wdm

takt:performedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "performed by"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The crew that performs the takt task. DTC v2 reifies this
        (AsPlannedProcess hasResourceAssignment -> ResourceAssignment requiresResource
        -> AsPlannedResource); takt uses a direct edge for simplicity, related to that
        pattern by seeAlso. Note IFC fans the other way (IfcRelAssignsToProcess assigns
        the crew TO the task)."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:Crew ;
    rdfs:seeAlso dtc:hasResourceAssignment , dtc:requiresResource , ifc:IfcRelAssignsToProcess ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt

takt:hasSuccessor a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "has successor"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The next takt task in execution order (default finish-start). The
        CHAIN of these edges is the TRAIN — a train is a path through the task graph,
        not a class. DTC reifies sequencing (hasPrecondition -> ProcessPrecondition +
        requiresProcess + hasSequenceType); takt uses a direct edge, related by
        seeAlso. This property is READING-AGNOSTIC; use the two subproperties to make
        the flow direction machine-detectable: takt:hasSuccessorSameZone (Reading A,
        the cross-trade convoy through one zone) and takt:hasSuccessorSameWagon
        (Reading B, one wagon's run across zones)."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:seeAlso dtc:requiresProcess , ifc:IfcRelSequence ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1061/9780784413517.168> ,        # frandson-2014-crc (predecessor field)
                   <https://doi.org/10.1080/01446193.2020.1824295> .    # lehtovaara-2021 (location vs trade flow)

takt:hasSuccessorSameZone a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf takt:hasSuccessor ;
    rdfs:label "has successor (same zone)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Reading A / LOCATION FLOW: the next task in the SAME takt zone —
        the next wagon of the cross-trade convoy pulling into this station. Successive
        tasks share their takt:performedIn zone and differ in wagon."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1080/01446193.2020.1824295> ,    # lehtovaara-2021 (location flow)
                   <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1350> .             # dlouhy-2016-three-level
takt:hasSuccessorSameWagon a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf takt:hasSuccessor ;
    rdfs:label "has successor (same wagon)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Reading B / TRADE FLOW: the same wagon's next occurrence in the
        NEXT takt zone — one trade tracked across the building. Successive tasks share
        their takt:instantiates wagon type and differ in zone."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1080/01446193.2020.1824295> ,    # lehtovaara-2021 (trade flow)
                   <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1181> .             # frandson-2015-lbms-vs-takt

takt:partOfProcess a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:label "part of process"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The on-site construction PROCESS this takt task is part of. Process
        membership together with takt:performedIn (space) and the rhythm (time) makes
        the task one cell of a Spatio-Temporal Breakdown Structure (TBS; Ljung 2026) —
        the process axis of the space x time x process breakdown (responsibility
        follows from crew + process together, not from this edge alone). DTC v2
        reifies decomposition the other way round (Process isDecomposedInto ->
        ProcessDecomposition hasChildProcess -> Process, with decompositionLevel);
        takt keeps the task-centric direct edge, related by seeAlso."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  dtc:Process ;
    rdfs:seeAlso dtc:isDecomposedInto , dtc:hasChildProcess , ifc:IfcRelNests ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://research.chalmers.se/publication/551855> .  # ljung-2026-tbs-integrated-delivery (TBS)

# =============================================================================
# DATATYPE PROPERTIES (6) — the takt rhythm + plan grid values DTC does not carry
# =============================================================================

takt:taktDuration a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "takt duration"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The fixed takt — the rhythm each wagon occupies in a zone — as an
        XSD duration, e.g. 'P7D' (one calendar week) or 'P5D'. NOTE: XSD durations
        have no week designator; write P7D, not the ISO-8601-only P1W. No rdfs:domain
        on purpose: assert it ONCE on the takt:TaktGraph for the plan-wide beat, or
        per takt:TaktTask where trains genuinely run different rhythms. This is the
        BEAT, distinct from a task's computed work content (which must fit within
        it — a consumer-side check, see docs ADR-10)."""@en ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:duration ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1297> ,        # haghsheno-2016-history (takt = fixed unit of time)
                   <https://doi.org/10.24928/2017/0297> .          # binninger-2017-technical-takt

takt:slot a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "takt slot"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The takt slot the task occupies — the 1-based column index in the
        plan grid. Planned calendar dates DERIVE: task start = takt:planStart +
        (slot - 1) x takt:taktDuration. (v0.5.0 moved this from the dissolved TaktTime
        class onto the task itself; see docs ADR-14.)"""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:integer ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (the grid)

takt:planStart a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "plan start"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The calendar date takt slot 1 begins — the single anchor that
        places the whole grid on the calendar. Planned task dates derive from it
        (see takt:slot); as-performed dates are observations and belong on DTC's
        as-performed side (dtc:startTime / dtc:endTime), outside this core."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktGraph ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:date ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.24928/2017/0297> ,          # binninger-2017-technical-takt (takt calendar mechanics)
                   <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt

takt:isMilestone a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is milestone"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """TRUE for milestone cells (e.g. 'Inflytt', 'Dem. bygghiss'). A
        milestone is not strictly 'one wagon in one zone for one takt' — flagging it
        on the task is a documented pragmatism mirroring IfcTask.IsMilestone, kept so
        every cell of the plan grid stays one TaktTask."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:boolean ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://technical.buildingsmart.org/standards/ifc/ifc-formats/ifcowl/> .

takt:isBuffer a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "is buffer"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """TRUE for capacity-buffer cells — the deliberately empty wagon slots
        takt planning uses to absorb variability. Buffers are what differentiate takt
        from LBMS-style planning (capacity buffers, not time buffers), so a takt
        vocabulary must be able to say 'this cell is a buffer'. A buffer task
        typically instantiates no wagon type."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:TaktTask ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:boolean ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://iglc.net/Papers/Details/1181> ,        # frandson-2015-lbms-vs-takt (capacity buffers)
                   <https://doi.org/10.24928/2017/0297> .          # binninger-2017-technical-takt (buffer mechanics)

takt:trade a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:label "trade"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """The trade / discipline a wagon type belongs to (e.g. 'drywall',
        'electrical') — the key the operand classification (which elements a task
        acts on) and trade-flow queries join on. A plain literal on purpose: owning
        a trade taxonomy is out of scope for the minimal core."""@en ;
    rdfs:domain takt:WagonType ;
    rdfs:range  xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/taktology> ;
    dcterms:source <https://doi.org/10.1002/bate.202200088> .      # becker-tschickardt-2023-bimtakt (trade-based wagons)

# =============================================================================
# IMPLEMENTER NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 1. ALIGNMENT BY REFERENCE. This file does not owl:imports DTC/BOT/top:/ifcOWL — it
#    only references their IRIs (keeps it lightweight, per ADR-3). Load DTC v2 and/or
#    BOT alongside when you want a reasoner to use their axioms; for TopologicPy,
#    merge takt.ttl into the TGraph knowledge graph BEFORE calling InferOntology
#    (TGraph's includeOntologyAxioms only injects TopologicPy's own axioms).
#
# 2. QUANTITIES ARE A CONSUMER CONCERN (out of the core; see docs ADR-10). To check
#    work content fits the takt, a consumer reads the area/volume of the takt:actsOn
#    operand (the trade subset, NOT the zone total) and applies its own rate/crew
#    model. TopologicPy carries quantities as TGraph dictionary values (keys "area",
#    "volume") and as top:Quantity records from IFC quantity sets; the published top:
#    v0.2.0 TTL declares NO top:area/top:volume datatype properties — see
#    docs/05-tgraph-pairing.md and ontology/alignments.lock.json before relying on
#    emitted quantity triples.
#
# 3. THE TRAIN is the takt:hasSuccessor chain (a path), not a class. Use the two
#    subproperties (hasSuccessorSameZone / hasSuccessorSameWagon) so location flow
#    and trade flow stay machine-distinguishable; both may coexist in one plan graph.
#
# 4. PLAN MEMBERSHIP is dtc:hasProcess (TaktGraph -> TaktTask), reused from DTC v2's
#    ConstructionSchedule. In a TGraph export, membership is also implicit in
#    top:hasNode / top:hasRelationship.
#
# 5. closeMatch != equivalentClass, and properties never closeMatch classes: classes
#    match IFC classes via skos:closeMatch; object properties reference the
#    objectified IfcRel* entities via rdfs:seeAlso only (different metamodel levels).
#
# 6. UPSTREAM PINS. Verified against: DTC v2 (modified 2024-07-31, imports BOT 0.3.2),
#    TopologicPy ontology v0.2.0 (modified 2026-06-27), ifcOWL IFC4 ADD2_TC1. Exact
#    hashes in ontology/alignments.lock.json; scripts/validate.py re-checks them.
# =============================================================================
